You are a senior .NET developer and a software architect. Act professionally: design clean architecture boundaries, organized folder structure, maintainable code, and production-grade conventions. Avoid hacks and messy structures.

Your task is to build a complete, production-grade solution consisting of:

1) A Console-based Website Generator (using .NET CLI internally)
2) A TemplatePack used by the generator
3) A fully working generated ASP.NET Core MVC website

You must output:
- The full folder structure first
- Then all source code files grouped by project
- No placeholders
- No TODOs
- Fully working code

============================================================
ADDITIONAL UI / TEMPLATE REQUIREMENTS (IMPORTANT)
============================================================

- The "base" template MUST be visually polished, modern, and corporate.
- It must be suitable for ALL industries (generic corporate look).
- Use Bootstrap-only layout and components (Bootstrap 5).
- The base template should include:
  - Modern navbar (brand + menu + language selector on the right)
  - Hero section on homepage
  - Services/Features section (cards)
  - About/Highlights section
  - Testimonials or clients section (optional but nice)
  - Contact section with address/phone/email + simple contact form UI (form UI only; no mail sending required)
  - Clean footer with links and social icons (Font Awesome)
- Typography, spacing, and responsive design must be excellent.
- Do not use custom UI frameworks. Only Bootstrap + minimal custom CSS (base.css + theme.css).
- Theme is a palette only (CSS variables recommended). The HTML structure stays the same.

- Admin UI under /manage must also be clean and usable:
  - Bootstrap-based admin layout (topbar or simple sidebar)
  - Tables for listing pages
  - Forms for edit/create pages
  - Summernote editor integration with a good UX
  - Basic validation messages styled with Bootstrap

============================================================
GLOBAL CONSTRAINTS (STRICT)
============================================================

- .NET 9 or .NET 10 selectable from console.
- Project creation MUST use dotnet CLI:
    dotnet new sln
    dotnet new mvc
- Database: EF Core + SQLite ONLY.
- DB file must be located in the same directory as the generated .csproj:
    {ProjectName}.db
- After generation:
    dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate
    dotnet ef database update
  must be executed automatically by the generator.

- NO caching allowed:
    No MemoryCache
    No ResponseCache
    No OutputCache
    No distributed cache

- No external logging frameworks.

- Error handling should use default ASP.NET Core error pipeline.

- Frontend libraries (CDN only):
    Bootstrap
    jQuery
    Font Awesome (fa fa-... syntax)

- Themes are CSS palettes only.
- Template defines HTML structure/layout.
- Theme is selected during generation and is permanent.

- Multi-language support:
    tr (default)
    en
    ru
  UI texts stored in JSON files:
    Resources/tr.json
    Resources/en.json
    Resources/ru.json

- URL format MUST be:
    /{culture}/{slug}

- Slug is single and always English (about, vision, mission, contact etc.)
- All languages share the same slug.

- Admin panel:
    No Area
    No separate project
    Single controller
    Route prefix: /manage

- Authentication:
    ASP.NET Core Cookie Authentication (NOT Identity)
    SlidingExpiration = true
    ExpireTimeSpan = 20 minutes
    Login and Logout MUST be POST
    SecurePolicy = SameAsRequest
    HttpOnly = true
    SameSite = Lax

- AdminUser password hashing:
    PBKDF2
    Stored as single string:
    PBKDF2$iterations$saltBase64$hashBase64

- HTML editor in admin:
    Summernote via CDN

- XSS Protection:
    Custom Regex-based sanitizer (temporary approach)

============================================================
HTML SANITIZER RULES (STRICT)
============================================================

Allowed tags:
p, br, b, strong, i, em, u,
ul, ol, li,
a,
h1, h2, h3, h4,
blockquote,
img

Allowed attributes:
- a: href, title
- img: src, alt, title

Allowed protocols:
- http
- https
- mailto (for <a>)
- img src: ONLY http or https
- data:, blob:, javascript: strictly forbidden

Global rules:
- Remove all on* attributes (onclick, onload, etc.)
- Remove style attribute entirely
- Remove script, iframe, object, embed completely
- For disallowed tags: remove the tag but keep inner content

============================================================
SOLUTION / FOLDER STRUCTURE (VERY IMPORTANT)
============================================================

Use a clean, organized structure like a real-world professional repo:

/WebsiteGenerator.sln
/src/
  /WebsiteGenerator/                  (console generator)
  /TemplatePack/                      (templates + resources + themes)
/docs/                                (optional: design notes)
/samples/                             (optional: sample generated output notes)

Inside TemplatePack:
- templates/base/                     (MVC template files as *.txt)
- resources/                          (tr/en/ru json as *.txt)
- themes/                             (theme css palettes as *.txt)

Inside generated MVC project:
- Controllers/
- Views/
- Views/Shared/
- wwwroot/css/
- wwwroot/js/
- Data/
- Domain/ (Entities)
- Services/ (Localization, Sanitization, Seo)
- Features/Manage/ (optional folder organization even if itâ€™s one controller; do NOT use Areas)
Keep naming and layering consistent and maintainable.

============================================================
GENERATOR PROJECT REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Project name: WebsiteGenerator
Type: Console App

Console flow:

1) Company Name
2) Output Directory (default: ./GeneratedSites)
3) .NET Version (9 or 10)
4) Template selection (default: base; keep future-ready)
5) Theme selection (light, dark, blue, green, purple, orange, red, teal)
6) Seed demo data? (Y/N)
7) Include English? (Y/N)
8) Include Russian? (Y/N)

NameSanitizer:
- Convert Turkish characters to ASCII
- Remove invalid characters
- Ensure valid Solution/Project name

ScaffoldService must:

- Create solution
- Create MVC project
- Add EF Core packages:
    Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite
    Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design

- Apply TemplatePack overlay
- Remove .txt extension from template files
- Perform token replacement:
    {{CompanyName}}
    {{SolutionName}}
    {{ProjectName}}
    {{DefaultTheme}}
    {{DotNetVersion}}

- Only replace tokens in text files:
    .cs
    .cshtml
    .json
    .css
    .js
    .csproj
    .sln
    .config
    .md

- Encoding must always be UTF-8 (no BOM).

- Run:
    dotnet restore
    dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate
    dotnet ef database update

============================================================
GENERATED MVC PROJECT REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Entities:

Page:
- Id
- Type (Home/About/Vision/Mission/Contact/Custom)
- Slug (unique, English)
- IsPublished
- CreatedAt
- UpdatedAt

PageTranslation:
- Id
- PageId
- Culture (tr/en/ru)
- Title
- HtmlContent
- SeoTitle
- SeoDescription
Unique(PageId, Culture)

SiteSetting:
- Id
- Key
- Value

AdminUser:
- Id
- Username
- PasswordHash
- CreatedAt
- LastLoginAt

DbContext:
- SQLite
- DB file:
    Data Source={ProjectName}.db
- Must resolve absolute path using ContentRoot

============================================================
ROUTING & CULTURE
============================================================

Route format:
    /{culture}/{slug}

- Default culture: tr
- Culture switch:
    POST /culture/set
    Set cookie
    Redirect to same slug in new culture

============================================================
SEED LOGIC
============================================================

- Migration always runs.
- Seed only runs if user selected seed.
- Seed runs at startup.
- If Page table already contains records, DO NOT seed.
- Seed must create:
    - Default pages (English slugs)
    - Translations based on selected languages
    - Default admin:
        Username: admin
        Password: Admin123!

============================================================
TEMPLATE PACK STRUCTURE
============================================================

TemplatePack/
    templates/
        base/
            All files must be stored as *.txt
            Must include:
              - Program.cs
              - AppDbContext + EF setup
              - Entities
              - Localization JSON loader
              - Sanitizer service
              - SEO schema (JSON-LD generator)
              - Controllers: PageController, CultureController, ManageController
              - Views: polished Bootstrap pages and Manage UI
              - Shared Layout: excellent responsive header/footer
    resources/
        tr.json.txt
        en.json.txt
        ru.json.txt
    themes/
        light.css.txt
        dark.css.txt
        blue.css.txt
        green.css.txt
        purple.css.txt
        orange.css.txt
        red.css.txt
        teal.css.txt

Selected theme must be copied as:
    wwwroot/css/theme.css

